  "text": "# Prometheus Metric Registration Patterns Analysis\n\nAcross kubernetes/kubernetes, grafana/grafana, and prometheus/prometheus, three distinct yet complementary patterns for Prometheus metric registration and exposure emerge:\n\n## Kubernetes: Custom Registry with Version Awareness\n\nKubernetes implements the most sophisticated pattern through a **custom KubeRegistry wrapper** (kubernetes/kubernetes:staging/src/k8s.io/component-base/metrics/registry.go). The KubeRegistry interface wraps prometheus.Registry and adds version-aware registration:\n\n- **Registerable interface** requires metrics to implement Create(version), ClearState(), and FQName() methods, enabling version-based hiding and deprecation tracking\n- **kubeRegistry.Register()** and **kubeRegistry.MustRegister()** check version compatibility before registration, automatically tracking deprecated metrics\n- **Custom metric types** (Counter, Gauge, Histogram, Summary) in counter.go, gauge.go, and histogram.go implement the Registerable interface with stability levels (STABLE, BETA, ALPHA)\n\nThe legacyregistry/registry.go file provides a global default registry instance with factory functions (MustRegister, RawMustRegister) for backward compatibility. The init() function registers native Prometheus collectors (ProcessCollector, GoCollector) using RawMustRegister, demonstrating how Kubernetes integrates Prometheus stdlib collectors.\n\n## Grafana: Layered Registration with Wrapper Patterns\n\nGrafana (grafana/grafana:pkg/infra/metrics/metrics.go) takes a **declarative approach with layered wrappers**:\n\n- Metrics are declared as package-level variables (MInstanceStart, MPageStatus, MApiStatus, etc.) across multiple types: Counter, CounterVec, Gauge, GaugeVec, Summary, SummaryVec, Histogram\n- The **init() function** (lines 262-718) explicitly creates all metrics using prometheus.NewCounter(), prometheus.NewGauge(), etc., with options like Namespace=\"grafana\" and Help text\n- **initMetricVars()** function (line 785) calls prometheus.Registerer.MustRegister() for batch registration\n- **ProvideService()** (pkg/infra/metrics/service.go) is a dependency injection point that initializes metrics during service startup by calling initMetricVars(reg)\n\nGrafana additionally wraps the Kubernetes legacyregistry (imported as k8s.io/component-base/metrics/legacyregistry) through:\n- **ProvideRegisterer()** returns legacyregistry.Registerer() to use Kubernetes' global registry\n- **addPrefixWrapper** (service.go) modifies metric names to add \"grafana_\" prefix\n- **NewMultiRegistry()** combines multiple gatherers (k8s and Prometheus default) with a deny-list for conflicts\n\nThis pattern shows Grafana's adoption of Kubernetes' metrics infrastructure while maintaining its own metrics namespace.\n\n## Prometheus: Direct Registration with Factory Patterns\n\nPrometheus (prometheus/prometheus:cmd/prometheus/main.go) uses **direct global registration** with a factory pattern for composable metrics:\n\n- Package-level variables (configSuccess, configSuccessTime) defined at lines 131-138 using prometheus.NewGauge()\n- **init() function** (line 147) calls prometheus.MustRegister(versioncollector.NewCollector(...)), demonstrating early registration\n- Metrics are registered at init-time before main() executes\n\nFor modular metric registration, Prometheus implements a **Metrics struct factory pattern** (discovery/metrics.go):\n- **NewManagerMetrics(registerer, sdManagerName)** creates a Metrics struct containing Counter, Gauge, and GaugeVec fields\n- Each metric is created individually (prometheus.NewGauge, prometheus.NewCounter) and stored in struct fields\n- Metrics are registered via **registerer.Register()** in a loop, with error handling\n- **Unregister()** method enables cleanup, essential for temporary discovery managers\n\nThis pattern enables dependency injection of registrers and lazy initialization of metric groups.\n\n## Key Differences\n\n1. **Registration Time**: Kubernetes uses version-aware delayed registration; Grafana uses init-time declarative setup; Prometheus uses init-time direct registration\n2. **Scope**: Kubernetes provides a stable, abstract registry interface; Grafana layers wrappers over it; Prometheus uses the default global registry\n3. **Composability**: Kubernetes handles deprecation internally; Grafana provides dependency injection through ProvideService; Prometheus provides factory functions for metric groups\n4. **Integration**: Kubernetes' legacyregistry serves as the underlying infra for both Kubernetes and Grafana; Prometheus stands independently with direct prometheus/client_golang usage"
